# loop through adata, save the raw matrix
obj = {}
for i in np.arange(len(adatas)):
    adata=adatas[i].copy()
    # Freeze state in raw 
    adata.raw = adata.copy()
    adata.layers['counts'] = adata.X.copy()
    
    obj[samples[i]] = adata.copy()

Integration with scVI¶

In [7]:
# Concatenate into one big adata 
# on raw counts
obj_list = list(obj.values())
obj_list = [obj_list[i].raw.to_adata() for i in np.arange(len(samples))]
# Concatenate
integrated_object = obj_list[0].concatenate(obj_list[1:])
# Add metadata column 
batch = ['0','1','2', '3', '4']
mouse=['R62', 'R62', 'WT', 'WT', 'WT']
engraft = ['hGPC', 'Unengrafted', 'hGPC', 'hGPC', 'Unengrafted']
origIdent=['R62_hGPC_1', 'R62_Unengrafted', 'WT_hGPC_1', 'WT_hGPC_2', 'WT_Unengrafted']

In [8]:
#
integrated_object.obs['mouse'] = integrated_object.obs['batch'].map(dict(zip(batch, mouse)))
integrated_object.obs['engraft'] = integrated_object.obs['batch'].map(dict(zip(batch, engraft)))
integrated_object.obs['orig.ident'] = integrated_object.obs['batch'].map(dict(zip(batch, origIdent)))

In [10]:
# Freeze the state in `.raw`
integrated_object.raw = integrated_object.copy()
# Preserve raw counts 
integrated_object.layers['counts'] = integrated_object.X.copy()
# Normalize to total library size 
sc.pp.normalize_total(integrated_object, target_sum=1e4)
# Log transform data 
sc.pp.log1p(integrated_object)

# Perform feature selection 
sc.pp.highly_variable_genes(integrated_object, n_top_genes = 2000, subset = True, layer = "counts", flavor="seurat_v3", batch_key = 'orig.ident')
In [11]:
scvi.model.SCVI.setup_anndata(integrated_object, layer = "counts", batch_key = 'orig.ident')
model = scvi.model.SCVI(integrated_object, n_layers = 1, n_latent = 10, n_hidden=128)
model.train(max_epochs=400)
integrated_object.obsm['X_scVI'] = model.get_latent_representation()
integrated_object.layers['scVI'] = model.get_normalized_expression(library_size=1e4)
